goals.question: What is the distribution of people across groups?

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='group_size', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['group_size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["group_size"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(x=data['group_size'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["group_size"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="group", y="group_size", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.axhline(y=data['group_size'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Group Size: {:.2f}'.format(data['group_size'].mean()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average group size?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.ylabel('Group Size')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="group", y="group_size", data=data, estimator=lambda x: len(x))
    ax.set(xlabel='Group', ylabel='Person Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people across groups?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_count = data.groupby('group').count().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.pie(group_count['person'], labels=group_count['group'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the most common group?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="group", hue="person", data=data, palette="Set2")
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of people across groups?")
    ax.set_xlabel("Group")
    ax.set_ylabel("Person Count")
    ax.legend(title="Person", loc="upper right")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
